The paper discusses the security and protection of personal information on mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the use of embedded sensors in smartphones for continuous user authentication, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The use of behavioral biometrics for authentication also involves multimedia processing (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.MM, and cs.CV.
